During a press briefing, White House Deputy Press Secretary Karine Jean-Pierre provided updates on various topics. She mentioned that President Biden convened the Major Economies Forum to address the climate crisis and announced new steps the United States is taking to support developing countries in taking stronger climate action. She also discussed Speaker McCarthy's proposal to cut benefits for American veterans and manufacturing jobs, and criticized the Florida Board of Education's decision to expand the state's "Don't Say Gay" law. Jean-Pierre highlighted the need to address gun violence and emphasized the importance of avoiding a default on the national debt. She also mentioned that the President will have a conversation with President Macron of France later in the day.